View Curve Data History

View the load and amendment history of curve data.

On the Curves tab, select History. The View Curve Data History dialog box will open.

In Display History for, select the curve you wish to view the history of.

This curve history will be detailed below. Column The number of columns of data associated with the file loaded. Start Depth The start depth of the data loaded. End Depth The end depth of the data loaded. File ID The File Name defined in the Load Data Wizard. If a curve is modified in any way, the type of modification will be detailed here (e.g [Edited], [Spliced] etc.) For more information on curve types, click here. Date Time The date and time of the file load or curve amendment event. User The logged-on user, responsible for the file load or curve amendment event. Vendor The supplied of the curve data. Type The type of data, such as LAS, TXT, ASCII. File Name The ‘Host’ or ‘Machine ID’, file path, file name (ID) and the license number. Note. You can resize this dialog box, as well as the widths of the data columns. The next time this dialog box is opened, it will use the last-sized widths.
